  "text": "We utilize data collected from 7 obese samples (case samples) and 7 age-matched lean control samples, using the 27K Illumina array (27,578 CpG sites [CITATION_1] ; NCBI's Gene Expression Omnibus accession number GSE25301). These 14 subjects were identified from the participants (n=534) in the Lifestyle, Adiposity, and Cardiovascular Health in Youth (LACHY) study, using the following inclusion criteria: (1) African American ancestry; (2) male; (3) having leukocyte DNA available; (4) obese cases having a body mass index (BMI) ≥ 99 th percentile for age and sex, and lean controls having BMI ≤ 10 th percentile for age and sex. The LACHY study consisted of roughly equal numbers of African American and European American adolescents, aged 14 to 18 years, of both sexes recruited from high schools in the Augusta, Georgia area [CITATION_2] .",
